{"body": "A kilobyte is 1024 bytes, the reason that some vendors refer to a kilobyte by 1000 bytes is beyond my understanding (simplicity?)\r\n\r\nThere's no need for us not to be precise and refer to it at 1024 bytes.  What would be a far better alternative is to create an option to the hash which would allow it to use both bases of 1000 and 1024, with 1024 being the default, so this doesn't break someone's application with the change.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1055342", "created_at": "2011-04-25T21:59:07Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/292#issuecomment-1055342", "updated_at": "2011-04-25T21:59:07Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 292, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/mnaser", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/a1ac9665158f95e477e424a733466951?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F28832233ef57763f51a3491dac3f139a.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser/received_events", "gravatar_id": "a1ac9665158f95e477e424a733466951", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "mnaser", "type": "User", "id": 435815, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mnaser/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52386324bd3543c151012475"}, "id": 1055342, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/292"}
